; Typical Mac user keyboard
; After remapping Ctrl, Alt and Win keys using this app:
; remapkey from Windows Server 2003 Resource Toolkit
; http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=17657

; LCtrl -> Win
; LAlt -> Ctrl
; LWin -> Alt

; You likely will need to make Ctrl+Tab to behave as Alt Tab
LCtrl & Tab:: AltTab

; Ctrl + }, Ctrl + { is better than Ctrl+Tab and Ctrl+Shift+Tab
LCtrl & }::Send {LCtrl down}{Tab}{LCtrl up}
LCtrl & {::Send {LCtrl down}{Shift down}{Tab}{Shift up}{LCtrl up}

; Ctrl + Space is more familiar than Ctrl + Shift
LCtrl & Space::Send {LCtrl down}{Shift}{LCtrl up}
^Space::^+

; And Alt + Space is more familiar than Win key
<!Space::
KeyWait Alt
KeyWait Space
Send {RWin}
return
